Woohoo! You have written your first C++ programs! [Congrats!]

In this lesson, you have learned:

    C++ is a general purpose coding language.
    C++ runs line by line, from top to bottom.
    std::cout is how you output to the terminal:

std::cout << "Good luck!\n";

Download the C++ Reference Guide: Hello World (Coming Soon!) to help you remember the content covered in this lesson.
Instructions
1.

Before we move on, let's write a letter to your future self.

In letter.cpp, let's add the following:

    Goal(s) for yourself.
    Today's date.

And click Run to mail the letter! [Hello World]
